%N A397579 a(n) = (4*Fibonacci(n) + Fibonacci(n+1))*Fibonacci(n+1)^3.
%C A397579 a(n) is the number of ways to tile a cross with four arms, each of length n (not counting the center cell) with squares and dominos. To illustrate, here is a cross with arm length n=3:
