%C A397579       |_|.
%H A397579 <a href="/index/Rec#order_05">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (5,15,-15,-5,1).
%F A397579 a(n) = A022095(n)*Fibonacci(n+1)^3 = A022095(n)*A056570(n+1).
%F A397579 a(n) = (9*Fibonacci(4*n+2) + 7*Fibonacci(4*n+3) + 8*Lucas(2*n+1)*(-1)^n - 6)/25.
%F A397579 a(n) = Fibonacci(n+1)^2*(Fibonacci(2*n+2) + 2*Fibonacci(n+1)*Fibonacci(n)).
%F A397579 a(n) = 5*a(n-1) + 15*a(n-2) - 15*a(n-3) - 5*a(n-4) + a(n-5).
%F A397579 G.f.: (3*x^3-8*x^2-1)/((x-1)*(x^2+3*x+1)*(x^2-7*x+1)). - _Alois P. Heinz_, Jul 01 2026
%e A397579 For n=3, here is one of the a(3) = 297 ways to tile it with squares and dominos:
